@node SAVEDOCUMENT
@remark File Commands

@{U}@{FG Highlight}SAVEDOCUMENT                                                                @{FG Text}@{UU}

This saves an open document.

@{B}savedocument@{UB} <DEFAULT | FILE filepath> [FILTER name]
[TEMPLATE] [progress] [mode] [DOCUMENT name]

DEFAULT    Saves using the existing filename and
           path.
FILE/s     The filename and path to which to save.
FILTER/s   The filter to use. Options: IFFDOC
           (default).
TEMPLATE/k Saves the document as a template.
progress/k Toggle to display a progress meter.
           Options: STATUS|NOSTATUS (default).
mode/k     The user prompt mode. Options: FORCE|
           ALERT|QUIET (default). Force overwrites
           without asking for confirmation, alert
           opens an alert box for confirmation, and
           quiet overwrites without confirmation but
           returns an error if a file is overwritten.
DOCUMENT   The document name. (Default=current)

Notes:

If DEFAULT is used and the file has not been
previously saved, the file dialog box will open.

ARexx Examples:

savedocument file 'Documents:Project' status

savedocument default nostatus force
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@prev PageStream3:Help/PGS.MD4/rx
@endnode

@node SAVEFONTPREFS
@remark AmigaOnly

@{U}@{FG Highlight}SAVEFONTPREFS                                                               @{FG Text}@{UU}

This saves the current font paths added in the Font
Preferences dialog box.

@{B}savefontprefs@{UB} <FILE filepath | DEFAULT>

FILE/s   The filename and path of the fontprefs file
         to save.
DEFAULT  Saves to PageStream3.fontprefs.

ARexx Examples:

savefontprefs file 'NewsletterFonts.fontprefs'

savefontprefs default
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

@node SAVEPRINTPREFS
@remark System Commands

@{U}@{FG Highlight}SAVEPRINTPREFS                                                              @{FG Text}@{UU}

This saves the current print settings in the Printing
Preferences dialog box.

@{B}saveprintprefs@{UB} <FILE filepath | DEFAULT>

FILE/s   The filename and path of the preferences
         file to which to save.
DEFAULT  Saves to the PageStream3 Preferences file.

Notes:

You can save printing preferences to a preferences
file containing other preference items.

ARexx Examples:

saveprintprefs default

saveprintprefs file 'PageStream3:ServiceBureau.prefs'
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

@node SAVESETTINGS
@remark System Commands

@{U}@{FG Highlight}SAVESETTINGS                                                                @{FG Text}@{UU}

This saves all of the program preferences.

@{B}savesettings@{UB} <FILE filepath | DEFAULT>

FILE/s   The filename and path of the preferences
         file to save.
DEFAULT  Saves to the PageStream3 Preferences file.

ARexx Examples:

savesettings default

savesettings file 'PageStream3:Letters.prefs'
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

@node SAVESNAPSHOT
@remark System Commands

@{U}@{FG Highlight}SAVESNAPSHOT                                                                @{FG Text}@{UU}

This saves the position and size of the current
window and all palettes.

@{B}savesnapshot@{UB} <FILE filepath | DEFAULT>

FILE/s   The filename and path of the preferences
         file to which to save.
DEFAULT  Saves to the PageStream3 Preferences file.

ARexx Examples:

savesnapshot default

savesnapshot file 'PageStream3:tiled.prefs'
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

@node SAVESTYLETAGS
@remark Style Commands

@{U}@{FG Highlight}SAVESTYLETAGS                                                               @{FG Text}@{UU}

This saves the current style tags in an IFF CTAG file.

@{B}savestyletags@{UB} <FILE filepath | ASK> [type] [progress]
[DOCUMENT name | WINDOW name | CHAPTER name]

FILE/s     The filename and path of the style tag
           file to save.
ASK        Opens a file selector to select the file.
type/k     The type of style tags to save. Options:
           ALL (default)|CHARACTER|PARAGRAPH|OBJECT|
           COLOR.
progress/k Toggle to display a progress meter.
           Options: STATUS|NOSTATUS (default).
DOCUMENT/s The document name. Default=current.
WINDOW/s   The window name. Default=current.
CHAPTER/s  The document/chapter name.
           Default=current.

Notes:

Colors are stored as color style tags, so colors are
also saved in IFF CTAG files.

ARexx Examples:

savestyletags file 'Work:Documents/MyColors' color

savestyletags ask status
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

@node SCALEOBJECT
@remark Object Commands

@{U}@{FG Highlight}SCALEOBJECT                                                                 @{FG Text}@{UU}

Scales objects by a percentage or relative amount.

@{B}scaleobject@{UB} <[SCALE scalex scaley] |
[OLDPOINT oldx oldy NEWPOINT newx newy]>
[ROTATE angle | SKEW slantangle twistangle]
[ABOUT <pointx | axisx> <pointy | axisy> |
ABOUTCENTER]
[DOCUMENT name | WINDOW name | OBJECTID number]

SCALE/d     The percentage scale.
OLDPOINT/d  The relative scale start point.
NEWPOINT/d  The relative scale end point.
ROTATE/d    The rotation angle. Default=0.
SKEW/d      The slant and twist angle.
SLANT/d     The slant angle.
TWIST/d     The twist angle.
ABOUT       The scale reference point.
pointx/d    The horizontal scale point.
axisx/k     The  horizontal scale axis. Options:
            LEFT|CENTER|RIGHT.
pointy/d    The vertical scale point.
axisy/k     The vertical scale axis. Options:
            TOP|MIDDLE|BOTTOM.
ABOUTCENTER Scales about its center. Default.
DOCUMENT/s  The document name. Default=current.
WINDOW/s    The window name. Default=current.
OBJECTID/i  The number of the object to manipulate.
            Default=current.
@remark newpanel
Notes:

When OLDPOINT and NEWPOINT are used to scale an
object, the amount the object is scaled is determined
by taking the differences between the horizontal and
vertical positions of these points and relating them
to the size of the object.

ARexx Examples:

scaleobject scale 80 100

scaleobject oldpoint 1.25 newpoint 4.15

scaleobject scale 50 50 about left top
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

@node SCREENTOBACK
@remark AmigaOnly

@{U}@{FG Highlight}SCREENTOBACK                                                                @{FG Text}@{UU}

Sends the screen on which PageStream is open to the
back of all screens.

@{B}screentoback@{UB} @{FG Fill}(no parameters)@{FG Text}

ARexx Examples:

screentoback
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

@node SCREENTOFRONT
@remark AmigaOnly

@{U}@{FG Highlight}SCREENTOFRONT                                                               @{FG Text}@{UU}

Brings the screen on which PageStream is open to the
front of all screens.

@{B}screentofront@{UB} @{FG Fill}(no parameters)@{FG Text}

ARexx Examples:

screentofront
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

@node SCRIPTPALETTE
@remark System Commands

@{U}@{FG Highlight}SCRIPTPALETTE                                                               @{FG Text}@{UU}

Displays the Script palette.

@{B}scriptpalette@{UB} [status] [AT pointx pointy]
[SIZE width height] [SAVE]

status/k The palette's display status. Options:
         SHOW|HIDE|TOGGLE.
AT/i     The palette position in pixels.
SIZE/i   The palette size in pixels.
SAVE     Saves the size, position and display status
         to the PageStream3 Preferences file.

Notes:

TOGGLE may not be used in conjunction with SAVE.

ARexx Examples:

scriptpalette toggle

scriptpalette show at 500 300 size 180 172 save

scriptpalette hide
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

@node SELECTMASTERPAGE
@remark Document Commands

@{U}@{FG Highlight}SELECTMASTERPAGE                                                            @{FG Text}@{UU}

Select the master page for a page and set how to show
its objects.

@{B}selectmasterpage@{UB} <NAME name> [PAGE number]
[stack] [status] [RIPPLE | TO number]

NAME/s   The master page name to use for the page.
PAGE/s   The number of the page to set.
         Default=current.
stack/k  The stack position. Options: INFRONT|INBACK.
status/k The master page's objects' display status.
         Options: SHOW|HIDE. Default=current.
RIPPLE   Sets the master page for all following pages
         until the next page which has been
         specifically set.
TO/s     Sets the master page for pages from PAGE to
         this page number.

ARexx Examples:

selectmasterpage name 'Default MPage' page 5 inback

selectmasterpage name '2 Column Layout' ripple

selectmasterpage 'Newsletter pages' page 3 to 9
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

@node SELECTOBJECT
@remark Object Commands

@{U}@{FG Highlight}SELECTOBJECT                                                                @{FG Text}@{UU}

Selects object(s).

@{B}selectobject@{UB} <NONE | ALL |
<OBJECTID [number] [how]> |
<RANGE left top right bottom [stack] [how]> |
<AT pointx pointy> [stack] [how]>>
[PAGE number | MPG name | WINDOW name]

NONE       Deselects all objects.
ALL        Selects all the objects on the page.
OBJECTID/i Selects an object by its ID.
RANGE/d    Selects objects inside these coordinates.
AT/d       Selects the objects at this point.

how/K      Specifies how to add new objects to an
           existing selection. Options:
           REPLACE   Replaces selected objects with
                     these objects.
           ADD       Adds to the selected object
                     list.
           REMOVE    Removes these objects from the
                     selected object list.
           TOGGLE    Adds these objects to the
                     selected object list if they are
                     not already selected; removes
                     them if they are selected.
           AND       Selects only the objects common
                     to the new selected objects and
                     to the previous selection list.
@remark newpanel
stack/k    Specifies which objects to select.
           Options:
           FRONTMOST Selects the frontmost object at
                     the point. Default for AT.
           BACKMOST  Selects the backmost object at
                     the point.
           EVERY     Selects all the objects in the
                     stack at the point. Default for
                     RANGE.
PAGE/s     The page number.
MPG/s      The master page name and side.
WINDOW/s   The window name. Default=current.

Notes:

You cannot select objects on more than one page
simultaneously. If an object is selected, selecting
an object on another page will deselect the first
object.

ARexx Examples:

selectobject at 4.24 5.382 backmost

selectobject range 1 1 5 5 remove

selectobject all
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

@node SELECTPOINT
@remark Drawing Commands

@{U}@{FG Highlight}SELECTPOINT                                                                 @{FG Text}@{UU}

Selects a path point.

@{B}selectpoint@{UB} [neighbor] [POINTINDEX point]
[DOCUMENT name | WINDOW name | OBJECTID number]

neighbor/k    Selects a neighboring point. Options:
              NEXT|PREVIOUS.
POINTINDEX/i  The number of the point to select.
              Default=selected point(s).
DOCUMENT/s    The document name. Default=current.
WINDOW/s      The window name. Default=current.
OBJECTID/i    The number of the object to manipulate.
              Default=current.

Notes:

Pointindex identification numbers are numbered from 0
starting with the first moveto in a path.

ARexx Examples:

selectpoint previous

selectpoint pointindex 23
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

@node SELECTTEXT
@remark Text Commands

@{U}@{FG Highlight}SELECTTEXT                                                                  @{FG Text}@{UU}

Selects a block of text.

@{B}selecttext@{UB} <what | AT pointx pointy [how] [stack] |
RANGE left top right bottom [how] [stack]>
[PAGE number | MPG name | DOCUMENT name | WINDOW name]

what/k     Specifies what text to select. Options:
           ALL       Selects all the text in the
                     article.
           PARAGRAPH Selects the current
                     paragraph(s).
           WORD      Selects the current word(s).
           FRAME     Selects the current frame(s).
           LINE      Selects the current line(s).
           NONE      Deselects selected text.
AT/d       Places the insertion point and selects the
           article at this position.
RANGE/d    Selects all the text in this area.
how/K      Specifies how to add new text to an
           existing selection. Options:
           REPLACE   Replaces selected text with this
                     text. Default.
           ADD       Adds to the selected text.
stack/k    Specifies which articles to select in.
           Options:
           FRONTMOST Selects in the frontmost article
                     at the point. Default.
           BACKMOST  Selects in the backmost article
                     at the point.
PAGE/s     The page number. Default=current insertion
           point.
@remark newpanel
MPG/s      The master page name and side.
DOCUMENT/s The document name. Default=current.
WINDOW/s   The window name. Default=current.

ARexx Examples:

selecttext all

selecttext range 1.25 3.3 1.75 5.25 add
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

@node SENDBACKWARD
@remark Object Commands

@{U}@{FG Highlight}SENDBACKWARD                                                                @{FG Text}@{UU}

Sends selected object(s) backward one level in the
stack.

@{B}sendbackward@{UB} [DOCUMENT name | WINDOW name |
OBJECTID number]

DOCUMENT/s The document name. Default=current.
WINDOW/s   The window name. Default=current.
OBJECTID/i The number of the object to manipulate.
           Default=current.

ARexx Examples:

sendbackward

sendbackward document 'project.doc'
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

@node SENDTOBACK
@remark Object Commands

@{U}@{FG Highlight}SENDTOBACK                                                                  @{FG Text}@{UU}

Sends selected object(s) backward to the bottom of
the stack.

@{B}sendtoback@{UB} [DOCUMENT name | WINDOW name |
OBJECTID number]

DOCUMENT/s The document name. Default=current.
WINDOW/s   The window name. Default=current.
OBJECTID/i The number of the object to manipulate.
           Default=current.

ARexx Examples:

sendtoback

sendtoback document 'project.doc'
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

@node SETALIGNMENT
@remark Text Commands

@{U}@{FG Highlight}SETALIGNMENT                                                                @{FG Text}@{UU}

Sets the paragraph alignment for the paragraph at the
insertion point, for selected paragraphs or for a
style tag.

@{B}setalignment@{UB} <alignment>
[DOCUMENT name | WINDOW name | STYLETAG name]

alignment/k Sets the alignment type. Options:
            JUSTIFY  Sets justified alignment.
            LEFT     Sets flush left alignment.
            CENTER   Sets centered alignment.
            RIGHT    Sets flush right alignment.
DOCUMENT/s The document name. Default=current.
WINDOW/s   The window name. Default=current.
STYLETAG/s Sets the attribute for a style tag.

ARexx Examples:

setalignment left styletag 'Body Text'

setalignment justify document 'project.doc'
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

@node SETARCDEFAULTS
@remark System Commands

@{U}@{FG Highlight}SETARCDEFAULTS                                                              @{FG Text}@{UU}

Sets the default type of arcs drawn.

@{B}setarcdefaults@{UB} [type] [ANGLES start end] [SAVE]

type/k    Sets the ellipse type. Options:
          PIE  A closed arc of an ellipse.
          ARC  An open arc of an ellipse
ANGLES/d  The starting and ending angles.
          Default=90°,360°.
SAVE      Saves the values to the PageStream3
          Preferences file.

ARexx Examples:

setarcdefaults pie angles 90 155.3 save
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

@node SETAREXXGADGET
@remark Dialog Box Commands

@{U}@{FG Highlight}SETAREXXGADGET                                                              @{FG Text}@{UU}

Resets a control's parameters. The dialog box and
control must first be added.

@{B}setarexxgadget@{UB} <dbox chandle> [LEFT left] [TOP top]
[WIDTH width] [HEIGHT height] [LABEL name]
[LABELPOS pos] [STRING text] [BORDER style]
[CHECKED status] [LIST handle] [CURRENT value]
[TOTAL value]

dbox/i     The dialog box handle.
dhandle/i  The control handle.
LEFT/i     The left edge of the control.
TOP/i      The top edge of the control.
WIDTH/i    The width of the control.
HEIGHT/i   The height of multiline and scrollist
           controls. Minimum=36
LABEL/s    The control's label.
LABELPOS/s The label position relative to the
           control. Options: LEFT|RIGHT|ABOVE|
           ABOVELEFT|ABOVERIGHT|BELOW|BELOWLEFT|
           BELOWRIGHT|CENTER|CENTERLEFT|CENTERRIGHT|
           LEFTABOVE|LEFTBELOW|RIGHTABOVE|RIGHTBELOW.
           Default=left except for checkbox=right.
STRING/s   The default text of a string, multiline
           or text control.
BORDER/k   The border type of a text control.
           Options: NONE|RAISED|RECESSED|SHINE|
           SHADOW|TEXT.
CHECKED/k  The default state of a checkbox. Options:
           TRUE|FALSE.
LIST/i     The list handle for a popup, cycle or
           scrollist control.
@remark newpanel
CURRENT/i  The default list item for a popup, cycle
           or scrollist, or the default slider
           position (decimal).
TOTAL/d    The range of a slider.

Notes:

The width and position of controls does not include
the label. Position is not applicable to exit
buttons because the label is centered on the button.

String controls are editable text fields; multilines
allow multiple lines of text. Text controls are non-
editable text displays.

Precede the character to underscore as a keyboard
shortcut in the label name. For example, "_Add" would
make "A" the keyboard shortcut for an "Add" control.

ARexx Examples:

setarexxgadget reqhandle check1 checked true

setarexxgadget req iList1 list fonts current 'Times'

setarexxgadget iDBox nametext 'Simple'

setarexxgadget req cyanslider current 15 total 100
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

@node SETARTICLE
@remark File Commands

@{U}@{FG Highlight}SETARTICLE                                                                  @{FG Text}@{UU}

Sets an article to be internal or external. Internal
articles are saved in the document file. External
articles store only the article filename and path in
the document file.

@{B}setarticle@{UB} [stored] [FILE filepath] [ARTICLE name |
DOCUMENT name | WINDOW name | ARTICLEID number]

stored/k    Specifies if the article is internal.
            Options: INTERNAL|EXTERNAL.
FILE/s      The filepath and name of the article.
ARTICLE/s   The name of the article to set.
DOCUMENT/s  The document name. Default=current.
WINDOW/s    The window name. Default=current.
ARTICLEID/i The number of the article.
            Default=current.

ARexx Examples:

setarticle internal

setarticle external article 'Story1'

setarticle external file 'Essay.2'

setarticle external path 'Text:Essay.2'
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

@node SETARTICLEDESC
@remark Text Commands

@{U}@{FG Highlight}SETARTICLEDESC                                                              @{FG Text}@{UU}

Sets the description of an article.

@{B}setarticledesc@{UB} <description> [ARTICLE name |
DOCUMENT name | WINDOW name | ARTICLEID number]

description/s The article description.
ARTICLE/s     The name of the article to set.
DOCUMENT/s    The document name. Default=current.
WINDOW/s      The window name. Default=current.
ARTICLEID/i   The number of the article.
              Default=current.

ARexx Examples:

setarticledesc 'Lead story on Olympics'

setarticledesc '1996 Olympics' article 'Story1'
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

@node SETARTICLENAME
@remark Text Commands

@{U}@{FG Highlight}SETARTICLENAME                                                              @{FG Text}@{UU}

Sets the name of an article.

@{B}setarticledesc@{UB} <name> [ARTICLE name |
DOCUMENT name | WINDOW name | ARTICLEID number]

name/s      The new name of the article.
ARTICLE/s   The name of the article to set.
DOCUMENT/s  The document name. Default=current.
WINDOW/s    The window name. Default=current.
ARTICLEID/i The number of the article.
            Default=current.

ARexx Examples:

setarticlename 'LeadStory'

setarticlename 'LeadStory' article 'Story1'
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

@node SETAUTOCOLUMNS
@remark System Commands

@{U}@{FG Highlight}SETAUTOCOLUMNS                                                              @{FG Text}@{UU}

Set the automatic column frame creation feature for
importing text.

@{B}setmeasurements@{UB} [status] [SAVE]

status/k  Automatic text frames status. Options:
          ON|OFF|TOGGLE.
SAVE      Saves to the PageStream3 Preferences file.

ARexx Examples:

setautocolumns on save

setautocolumns toggle
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

@node SETBACKUP
@remark System Commands

@{U}@{FG Highlight}SETBACKUP                                                                   @{FG Text}@{UU}

Changes the autobackup and autosave status.

@{B}setbackup@{UB} [AUTOBACKUP status [COUNT number]]
[AUTOSAVE status [INTERVAL time]] [PATH filepath]
[SAVE]

status/k     Sets the feature status. Options:
             ON|OFF|TOGGLE.
AUTOBACKUP/k Sets the autobackup status.
COUNT/i      Sets the number of backup copies.
AUTOSAVE/k   Sets the autosave status.
INTERVAL/i   Sets the autosave interval in minutes.
PATH/s       Sets the autosave and autobackup path.
SAVE         Saves to the PageStream3 Preferences
             file.

Notes:

The TOGGLE parameter may not be used in conjunction
with the SAVE parameter.

ARexx Examples:

setbackup autobackup toggle count 3 path 'work:back'

setbackup autosave off

setbackup autobackup on autosave on interval 5 save
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

@node SETBASELINE
@remark Text Commands

@{U}@{FG Highlight}SETBASELINE                                                                 @{FG Text}@{UU}

Sets the baseline offset at the insertion point, for
selected text or for a style tag. This command has no
menu equivalent since super and subscripts can be
created with Type Style commands.

@{B}setbaseline@{UB} <offset>
[DOCUMENT name | WINDOW name | STYLETAG name]

offset/d    The baseline offset.
DOCUMENT/s  The document name. Default=current.
WINDOW/s    The window name. Default=current.
STYLETAG/s  Sets the attribute for a style tag.

ARexx Examples:

setbaseline 6

setbaseline '0p2'

setbaseline '0.5"' document 'project.doc'

setbaseline 8 styletag 'Superior Text'
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

@node SETBASELINELEADING
@remark Text Commands

@{U}@{FG Highlight}SETBASELINELEADING                                                          @{FG Text}@{UU}

Sets the leading method at the insertion point, for
selected text or for a style tag.

@{B}setbaselineleading@{UB} <method amount>
[DOCUMENT name | WINDOW name | STYLETAG name]

method/k   The leading method. Options:
           RELATIVE  Sets the baseline to a relative
                     value from the top of the slug.
           TRELATIVE Sets to relative top of caps
                     leading. The baseline is a
                     relative value measured from the
                     hightest point of any character
                     in the font.
           TFIXED    Sets to top of caps leading. The
                     baseline is a fixed value
                     measured from the highest point
                     of any character in the font.
                     font. No interface equivalent.
           FIXED     Sets the baseline to a fixed
                     value offset from the top of
                     the slug. No interface
                     equivalent.
amount/d   The baseline or top of caps offset.
DOCUMENT/s The document name. Default=current.
WINDOW/s   The window name. Default=current.
STYLETAG/s Sets the attribute for a style tag.

ARexx Examples:

setbaselineleading relative 66

setbaselineleading fixed 8 styletag 'Body Text'
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

@node SETBITMAPEDITOR
@remark AmigaOnly

@{U}@{FG Highlight}SETBITMAPEDITOR                                                             @{FG Text}@{UU}

Set the default picture editor script for the Sned to
Editor command.

@{B}setbitmapeditor@{UB} <script> [SAVE]

script/s  The filename and path of the script to use.
SAVE      Saves to the PageStream3 Preferences file.

ARexx Examples:

setbitmapeditor 'Scripts/SendtoBME.rexx'
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

@node SETBOLD
@remark Text Commands

@{U}@{FG Highlight}SETBOLD                                                                     @{FG Text}@{UU}

Sets the bold style option at the insertion point,
for selected text or for a style tag.

@{B}setbold@{UB} <toggle> [DOCUMENT name | WINDOW name |
STYLETAG name]

toggle/k   Toggles on or off the style.
           Options: on|off.
DOCUMENT/s The document name. Default=current.
WINDOW/s   The window name. Default=current.
STYLETAG/s Sets the attribute for a style tag.

ARexx Examples:

setnormal on

setnormal off document 'project.doc'
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

@node SETBOXDEFAULTS
@remark System Commands

@{U}@{FG Highlight}SETBOXDEFAULTS                                                              @{FG Text}@{UU}

Sets the default radii for round cornered boxes.

@{B}setboxdefaults@{UB} [type]
[CORNER radius | ECORNER radiusx radiusy] [SAVE]

type/k    Sets the corner type. Options:
          NORMAL   Square corners. Corner radii=0.
          ROUND    Outward rounded corners.
          SCALLOP  Inward rounded corners.
          BEVEL    Angled corners.
          INSET    Square insert corners.
CORNER/d  The corner radius.
ECORNER/d The elliptical corner radius.
SAVE      Saves to the PageStream3 Preferences file.

ARexx Examples:

setboxdefaults round corner 0.25 save
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

@node SETBULLET
@remark Text Commands

@{U}@{FG Highlight}SETBULLET                                                                   @{FG Text}@{UU}

Sets the bullet paragraph type for the paragraph at
the insertion point, for selected paragraphs or for a
style tag.

@{B}setbullet@{UB}  <OFF | ON <character/S
[FONT name] [STYLE name]>>
[DOCUMENT name | WINDOW name | STYLETAG name]

OFF        Toggles automatic bullets off.
ON         Toggles automatic bullets on
FONT/s     The name of the font. Default=current.
STYLE/s    The style of the font. Default=current.
DOCUMENT/s The document name. Default=current.
WINDOW/s   The window name. Default=current.
STYLETAG/s Sets the attribute for a style tag.

Notes:

To set the paragraph type to Normal, set the bullet
and drop cap options to off.

You can enter a unicode value if the character for
the bullet is not part of the standard character set.
Type a backslash followed by the unicode value for a
unicode character.

ARexx Examples:

setbullet on \8226

setbullet on '·' font 'AGaramond-Semibold'

setbullet off styletag 'Body Text'
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

@node SETBUSYREQUESTER
@remark Dialog Box Commands

@{U}@{FG Highlight}SETBUSYREQUESTER                                                            @{FG Text}@{UU}

Sets the thermometer and message for an open busy
dialog box.

@{B}setbusyrequester@{UB} <handle> [MESSAGE text]
[THERMOMETER status] [ABORT status] [TOTAL value]
[CURRENT value]

handle/i       The handle of the dialog box to set.
MESSAGE/s      The single line of text to display.
THERMOMETER/k  Specifies whether the thermometer is
               used. Options: ENABLED|DISABLED.
ABORT          Specifies whether the Stop button is
               available. Options: ENABLED|DISABLED.
TOTAL/i        Sets the thermometer's total value.
CURRENT/i      Sets the thermometer's current value.

ARexx Examples:

openbusyrequester message 'Thinking...' thermometer ¬
   enabled total 100 current 0
   bh=RESULT
do for i = 1 to 100
   /* script does something here */
   /* abort if stop is clicked else set mometer */
   getbusyrequester bh
   if result=1 then break else setbusyrequester bh ¬
      current i
end i
closebusyrequester bh
@endnode

@node SETCASE
@remark Text Commands

@{U}@{FG Highlight}SETCASE                                                                     @{FG Text}@{UU}

Sets the case of text at the insertion point or for
selected text. Unlike the MAKERUPPERCASE and related
commands, this command does not change the case of
the letters, but merely displays and prints them as
the set case because the original case is retained.
If the OFF parameter is later used, the original case
will be re-applied. This command has no interface
equivalent.

@{B}setcase@{UB} <case>

case/k  Sets the case. Options:
        OFF         Does not force set the case.
        UPPER       Sets the text to uppercase.
        LOWER       Sets the text to lowercase.
        CAPITALIZED Sets the text to capitalized.

ARexx Examples:

setcase capitalized
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

@node SETCHAPTERDESC
@remark Document Commands

@{U}@{FG Highlight}SETCHAPTERDESCRIPTION                                                       @{FG Text}@{UU}

Sets the description of an open chapter.

@{B}setchapterdesc@{UB} <text> [CHAPTER name | WINDOW name]

text/s    The chapter description.
CHAPTER/s The document/chapter name. Default=current.
WINDOW/s  The window name. Default=current.

ARexx Examples:

setchapterdescription 'For discussion of particles.'
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

@node SETCHAPTERNAME
@remark Document Commands

@{U}@{FG Highlight}SETCHAPTERNAME                                                              @{FG Text}@{UU}

Sets the name of an open chapter.

@{B}setchaptername@{UB} <name> [CHAPTER name | WINDOW name]

name/s    The new name of the chapter.
CHAPTER/s The document/chapter name. Default=current.
WINDOW/s  The window name. Default=current.

ARexx Examples:

setchaptername 'Part IV' window 'Book.doc~View.1'
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

@node SETCHAPTERNUMBERING
@remark Document Commands

@{U}@{FG Highlight}SETCHAPTERNUMBERING                                                         @{FG Text}@{UU}

Sets the chapter numbering system for chapters in a
chapter or document. All chapters inside the
specified (or current) chapter or document will be
affected.

@{B}setchapternumbering@{UB} [START <AUTOMATIC |
CUSTOM number>] [MASTERPAGE name] [FORMAT type]
[LANGUAGE name] [PREFIX string]
[DOCUMENT name | CHAPTER name | WINDOW name]

START/k     The numbering method. Options:
            AUTOMATIC  Automatic numbering.
            CUSTOM/i   Manual numbering and the start
                       number.
MASTERPAGE  The master page to use for blank pages.
FORMAT/k    The number format: DEFAULT|LONG|ARABIC|
            ROMANUPPER|ROMANLOWER|ALPHAUPPER|
            ALPHALOWER.
LANGUAGE/s  The number language:
            DEFAULT    Document/chapter default.
            AMERICAN   American English.
            ENGLISH    International English.
            FRANCAIS   French.
            DEUTSCH    German.
PREFIX/s    The prefix string.
DOCUMENT/s  The document name. Default=current.
WINDOW/s    The window name. Default=current.
CHAPTER/s   The document/chapter name.
            Default=current.
@remark newpanel
Notes:

The START parameter is required because you can
actually set the ending chapter number. This feature
is not supported at this time, but the START
parameter is required for future compatibility.

ARexx Examples:

setchapternumbering start manual 2
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

@node SETCHARACTERSTYLE
@remark Style Commands

@{U}@{FG Highlight}SETCHARACTERSTYLE                                                           @{FG Text}@{UU}

Sets the character style for the text at the
insertion point or for selected text.

@{B}setcharacterstyle@{UB} <style>
[DOCUMENT name | WINDOW name | STYLETAG name]

style/s    The character style to set.
DOCUMENT/s The document name. Default=current.
WINDOW/s   The window name. Default=current.
STYLETAG/s --unknown--

ARexx Examples:

setcharacterstyle 'Body Text'
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

@node SETCOLOR
@remark Color Commands

@{U}@{FG Highlight}SETCOLOR                                                                    @{FG Text}@{UU}

Sets the color for an object or text, or for a style
tag. If object or text is chosen and nothing is
selected, it sets the color for future objects or
text, as applicable.

@{B}setcolor@{UB} [TINT value] [method] [type]
<BLACK | WHITE | GRAY value | RGB red green blue |
CMYK cyan magenta yellow black | PANTONE name |
HLS hue lightness saturation | HSV hue saturation
value> [ALL | FILL | STROKENUMBER number]
[COLORNUMBER number] [what] [DOCUMENT name |
WINDOW name | OBJECTID number | STYLETAG name]

TINT/d         The tint percentage.
method/k       The print method. Options:
               KNOCKOUT  Knocks out the background.
               OVERPRINT Prints over the background.
type/k         The color type. Options:
               PROCESS   A process (separable) color.
               SPOT      A spot (mechanical) color.
BLACK          Sets the color to black.
WHITE          Sets the color to white.
GRAY/d         Sets the color to a grayscale.
RGB/d          Defines a RGB color.
CMYK/d         Defines a CMYK color.
PANTONE/s      Selects a PANTONE color.
HLS/d          Defines an HLS color.
HSV/d          Defines an HSV color.
ALL            Sets the fill and stroke. Default.
FILL           Sets the fill only.
STROKENUMBER/i Sets a stroke only. See notes.
@remark newpanel
COLORNUMBER    Sets a gradient's TO color.
what/k         Specifies what to set. Options:
               OBJECT    The object. Default.
               TEXT      The text.
               SHADOW    The text shadow.
               REVERSE   The text reverse.
               UNDERLINE The text underline.
               OUTLINE   The text outline.
DOCUMENT/s     The document name. Default=current.
WINDOW/s       The window name. Default=current.
OBJECTID/i     The number of the object to
               manipulate. Default=current.
STYLETAG/s     Sets the attribute for a style tag.

Notes:

STROKENUMBER: Strokes are numbered from 0. This is
different than the program interface which numbers
them from 1.

COLORNUMBER: If Basic fills are used, or if you are
setting stroke color, the color number is always 0
and does not need to be specified. This is used for
gradient, radial and shape fills. Color number 0 is
the From color and 1 is the To color.

TINT: This parameter is equivalent to the Tint
control in the Edit Color dialog box, and not the
Tint controls in the Line & Fill dialog box.
@remark newpanel
ARexx Examples:

setcolor black

setcolor tint 50 PANTONE 'PANTONE 120 CV' ¬
   strokenumber 1 object

setcolor cmyk 25 43 0 12 shadow
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

@node SETCOLORCOUNT
@remark Color Commands

@{U}@{FG Highlight}SETCOLORCOUNT                                                               @{FG Text}@{UU}

Sets the number of colors for the fill or stroke of
an object or text, or for a style tag. If object or
text is chosen and nothing is selected, it sets the
number of colors for future objects or text, as
applicable.

Basic fills have one color, while gradient, radial
and shape fills have two colors. This command is
necessary because future versions may support more
than two colors.

@{B}setcolorcount@{UB} <count> [ALL | FILL | STROKENUMBER
number] [COLORNUMBER number] [what] [DOCUMENT name |
WINDOW name | OBJECTID number | STYLETAG name]

count/i        The number of colors. Default=1.
ALL            Sets the fill and stroke. Default.
FILL           Sets the fill only.
STROKENUMBER/i Sets a stroke only. See notes.
COLORNUMBER    Sets a gradient's TO color.
what/k         Specifies what to set. Options:
               OBJECT    The object. Default.
               TEXT      The text.
               SHADOW    The text shadow.
               REVERSE   The text reverse.
               UNDERLINE The text underline.
               OUTLINE   The text outline.
DOCUMENT/s     The document name. Default=current.
WINDOW/s       The window name. Default=current.
OBJECTID/i     The number of the object to
               manipulate. Default=current.
STYLETAG/s     Sets the attribute for a style tag.
@remark newpanel
Notes:

Use the SETFILL command to set the fill type to
gradient, radial or shape, then use this command to
set the color count to 2. If you set the fill to
basic, then set the color count to 1.

If Basic fills are used, or if you are setting stroke
color, the color number is always 0 and does not need
to be specified. This is used for gradient, radial
and shape fills. Color number 0 is the From color and
1 is the To color.

STROKENUMBER: Strokes are numbered from 0. This is
different than the program interface which numbers
them from 1.

ARexx Examples:

setcolorcount 2

setcolorcount 1 strokenumber 1 object
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

@node SETCOLORSTYLE
@remark Color Commands

@{U}@{FG Highlight}SETCOLORSTYLE                                                               @{FG Text}@{UU}

Sets the color style tag for the selected object(s)
or text, as specified. If no objects or text is
selected, it sets the color style for future objects
or text.

@{B}setcolorstyle@{UB} <color> [ALL | FILL | STROKENUMBER
number] [COLORNUMBER number] [what] [DOCUMENT name |
WINDOW name | OBJECTID number | STYLETAG name]

color/s        The color style to set.
ALL            Sets the fill and stroke. Default.
FILL           Sets the fill only.
STROKENUMBER/i Sets a stroke only. See notes.
@remark newpanel
COLORNUMBER    Sets a gradient's TO color.
what/k         Specifies what to set. Options:
               OBJECT    The object. Default.
               TEXT      The text.
               SHADOW    The text shadow.
               REVERSE   The text reverse.
               UNDERLINE The text underline.
               OUTLINE   The text outline.
DOCUMENT/s     The document name. Default=current.
WINDOW/s       The window name. Default=current.
OBJECTID/i     The number of the object to
               manipulate. Default=current.
STYLETAG/s     --unknown--
@remark newpanel
Notes:

STROKENUMBER: Strokes are numbered from 0. This is
different than the program interface which numbers
them from 1.

COLORNUMBER: If Basic fills are used, or if you are
setting stroke color, the color number is always 0
and does not need to be specified. This is used for
gradient, radial and shape fills. Color number 0 is
the From color and 1 is the To color. This format is
used to allow future expansion. Default=0.

ARexx Examples:

setcolorstyle 'NeonPink'

setcolorstyle 'Orange' all text

setcolorstyle 'Red' strokenumber 2

setcolorstyle 'Blue' colornumber 1 object
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

@node SETCOLORTINT
@remark Color Commands

@{U}@{FG Highlight}SETCOLORTINT                                                                @{FG Text}@{UU}

Sets the color tint for an object or text, or for a
style tag. If object or text is chosen and nothing is
selected, it sets the color for future objects or
text, as applicable.

@{B}setcolortint@{UB} <value> [ALL | FILL | STROKENUMBER
number] [COLORNUMBER number] [what] [DOCUMENT name |
WINDOW name | OBJECTID number | STYLETAG name]

value/d        The tint percentage.
ALL            Sets the fill and stroke. Default.
FILL           Sets the fill only.
STROKENUMBER/i Sets a stroke only. See notes.
COLORNUMBER    Sets a gradient's TO color.
what/k         Specifies what to set. Options:
               OBJECT    The object. Default.
               TEXT      The text.
               SHADOW    The text shadow.
               REVERSE   The text reverse.
               UNDERLINE The text underline.
               OUTLINE   The text outline.
DOCUMENT/s     The document name. Default=current.
WINDOW/s       The window name. Default=current.
OBJECTID/i     The number of the object to
               manipulate. Default=current.
STYLETAG/s     Sets the attribute for a style tag.
@remark newpanel
Notes:

STROKENUMBER: Strokes are numbered from 0. This is
different than the program interface which numbers
them from 1.

COLORNUMBER: If Basic fills are used, or if you are
setting stroke color, the color number is always 0
and does not need to be specified. This is used for
gradient, radial and shape fills. Color number 0 is
the From color and 1 is the To color.

This command is equivalent to the Tint controls in
the Line & Fill dialog box.

ARexx Examples:

setcolortint 50
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

@node SETCOLUMNDEFAULTS
@remark System Commands

@{U}@{FG Highlight}SETCOLUMNDEFAULTS                                                           @{FG Text}@{UU}

Sets the default type of columns drawn.

@{B}setcolumndefaults@{UB} [COLUMNS number] [GUTTER space]
[fill] [SAVE]

COLUMNS/i  The number of columns in the frame.
GUTTER/d   The space between columns.
fill/k     Sets the column fill type. Options:
           OPAQUE      Sets the fill to solid white.
           TRANSPARENT Sets the fill to none.
SAVE       Saves to the PageStream3 Preferences file.

ARexx Examples:

setcolumndefaults columns 3 gutter 0.25 transparent ¬
   save
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

@node SETCOLUMNGUIDES
@remark Document Commands

@{U}@{FG Highlight}SETCOLUMNGUIDES                                                             @{FG Text}@{UU}

Change the column guides of a master page in a
document or chapter.

@{B}setcolumnguides@{UB} <columns gutter>
[SAVE] [MASTERPAGE name]

columns/i    The number of columns in the layout.
gutter/d     The space between columns.
SAVE         Saves to the PageStream3 Preferences
             file.
MASTERPAGE/s The master page name. Default=current.

ARexx Examples:

setcolumnguides 3 0.25 masterpage '3 Column Layout'
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

@node SETDEFAULTTABSTOP
@remark Text Commands

@{U}@{FG Highlight}SETDEFAULTTABSTOP                                                           @{FG Text}@{UU}

Sets the default tab spacing at the insertion point,
for selected paragraphs or for a style tag.

@{B}setdefaulttabstop@{UB}  <amount>
[DOCUMENT name | WINDOW name | STYLETAG name]

amount/d   The tab spacing.
DOCUMENT/s The document name. Default=current.
WINDOW/s   The window name. Default=current.
STYLETAG/s Sets the attribute for a style tag.

ARexx Examples:

setdefaulttabstop 0.333in

setdefaulttabstop 10mm styletag 'Body Text'
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

@node SETDIMENSIONS
@remark Document Commands

@{U}@{FG Highlight}SETDIMENSIONS                                                               @{FG Text}@{UU}

Change the dimensions of a master page in a document
or chapter.

@{B}setdimensions@{UB} <width height> [orientation] [sides]
[SAVE] [MASTERPAGE name]

width          The master page width.
height         The master page height.
ORIENTATION/k  The orientation: PORTRAIT|LANDSCAPE.
SIDES/k        The number of sides: SINGLE|DOUBLE.
SAVE           Saves to the PageStream3 Preferences
               file.
MASTERPAGE/s   The master page name. Default=current.

ARexx Examples:

setdimensions 8.5 14 portrait double

setdimensions 17 11 masterpage 'Ledger Sheet'
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

@node SETDOCUMENTDESC
@remark Document Commands

@{U}@{FG Highlight}SETDOCUMENTDESCRIPTION                                                      @{FG Text}@{UU}

Sets the description of an open document.

@{B}setdocumentdesc@{UB} <text> [DOCUMENT name]

text/s     The document description.
DOCUMENT/s The document name. Default=current.

ARexx Examples:

setdocumentdescription 'Lesson 3 exam'
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

@node SETDOCUMENTNAME
@remark Document Commands

@{U}@{FG Highlight}SETDOCUMENTNAME                                                             @{FG Text}@{UU}

Changes the name of an open document.

@{B}setdocumentname@{UB} <name> [DOCUMENT name]

name/s     The new name of the document.
DOCUMENT/s The document name. Default=current.

ARexx Examples:

setdocumentname 'Project.doc' document 'Untitled 1'
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

@node SETDOCUMENTPATH
@remark System Commands

@{U}@{FG Highlight}SETDOCUMENTPATH                                                             @{FG Text}@{UU}

Sets the default file path for opening and saving
documents.

@{B}setdocumentpath@{UB} <filepath> [SAVE]

filepath/s The path for the files.
SAVE       Saves to the PageStream3 Preferences file.

ARexx Examples:

setdocumentpath 'PageStream3:Documents'
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

@node SETDOCUMENTSTATUS
@remark Document Commands

@{U}@{FG Highlight}SETDOCUMENTSTATUS                                                           @{FG Text}@{UU}

Changes the saved status of an open document.

@{B}setdocumentstatus@{UB} <status> <DOCUMENT name>

status/k   Sets the document status. Options:
           CHANGED   Marks the document as changed.
           UNCHANGED Marks the document as unchanged.
DOCUMENT/s The document name. Default=current.

ARexx Examples:

setdocumentstatus changed document 'Project.doc'
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

@node SETDOUBLECLICK
@remark Object Commands

@{U}@{FG Highlight}SETDOUBLECLICK                                                              @{FG Text}@{UU}

Set the action to be performed when an object is
double clicked.

@{B}setdoubleclick@{UB} [OFF | MACRO name | REQUESTER name]
[SAVE]

OFF         Sets to no action.
MACRO       Sets to any internal PageStream script.
REQUESTER/k Sets to a command. Options: LINEFILL|
            RUNAROUND|DUPLICATE|TRANSFORM|ROTATE|
            MOVE|ALIGN|LOCK|UNLOCK|BRINGTOFRONT|
            BRINGFORWARD|SENDTOBACK|SENDBACKWARD.
SAVE        Saves to the PageStream3 Preferences file.

ARexx Examples:

setdoubleclick rotate

setdoubleclick macro 'ToggleFill' save
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

@node SETDRAWING
@remark Text Commands

@{U}@{FG Highlight}SETDRAWING                                                                  @{FG Text}@{UU}

Sets the name and description of a drawing object.

@{B}setdrawing@{UB} [NAME name] [DESC description]
[DOCUMENT name | WINDOW name | OBJECTID number]

NAME/s      The new name of the object.
DESC/s      The new description of the object.
DOCUMENT/s  The document name. Default=current.
WINDOW/s    The window name. Default=current.
OBJECTID/i  The number of the object to manipulate.
            Default=current.

ARexx Examples:

setdrawing name 'CorporateLogo'
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

@node SETDRAWINGEDITOR
@remark AmigaOnly

@{U}@{FG Highlight}SETDRAWINGEDITOR                                                            @{FG Text}@{UU}

Set the default drawing editor script for the Send to
Editor command.

@{B}setdrawingeditor@{UB} <script> [SAVE]

script/s  The filename and path of the script to use.
SAVE      Saves to the PageStream3 Preferences file.

ARexx Examples:

setdrawingeditor 'Scripts/SendtoArtExp.rexx'
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@endnode

@node SETDUPLICATEDEFAULTS
@remark System Commands

@{U}@{FG Highlight}SETDUPLICATEDEFAULTS                                                        @{FG Text}@{UU}

Set the default duplicate offset.

@{B}setduplicatedefaults@{UB} <offsetx offsety> [SAVE]

offsetx/d  The horizontal offset.
offsety/d  The vertical offset.
SAVE       Saves to the PageStream3 Preferences file.

ARexx Examples:

setduplicatedefaults 0.25 0.25 save
@toc PageStream3:Help/PGS.HEL/MAIN
@next PageStream3:Help/PGS.MD6/setfill
@endnode
